criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. right handed，age between 18 and 45 years old, college degree or above;

          2. match the Rome III criteria on FD;

          3. no local organic disease by gastroscope examination;

          4. before entering the study, without taking any prokinetic agents at least 15days and
             participating in other clinical study;

          5. signing an informed consent in writing by the participant or the immediate family
             member.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. consciousness, cannot express subjective symptoms and psychiatric participants;

          2. participants with advanced cancer or other serious wasting diseases, easy to be
             infected and bleeding;

          3. complicating with severe cardiovascular, hepatic,nephritic,digestive, hematopoietic
             system diseases;

          4. impregnate or lactation female;

          5. severe depression and anxiety symptoms;

          6. female with serious dysmenorrhea;

          7. obvious headache, migraine, history of head injury.
